Judul: Israeli spacecraft crash-lands on Moon: Attempt to put first privately funded lander on the Moon fails.
Abstrak: The Israeli spacecraft Beresheet crashlanded on the Moon on 11 April after experiencing apparent engine trouble moments before it was scheduled to touch down. The mishap ended the mission’s goal of becoming the first privately funded craft to make a controlled landing on the Moon.
